ee that the <code class=\"language-text\">/var/lib/mysql</code> needs to be mounted separately to preserve data so that the container can be recreated.</p><p>First, let's try with bind mount:</p><div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"dockerfile\"><pre class=\"language-dockerfile\"><code class=\"language-dockerfile\">version<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'3'</span>\n\nservices<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n  db<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    image<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> mysql\n    environment<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> example\n    <span class=\"token comment\">#command: --default-authentication-plugin=mysql_native_password</span>\n    volumes<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> ./mysql<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>/var/lib/mysql</code></pre></div><p>And now <code class=\"language-text\">docker-compose up</code></p><p>Then, with a <strong>volume</strong></p><div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"dockerfile\"><pre class=\"language-dockerfile\"><code class=\"language-dockerfile\">version<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'3'</span>\n\nservices<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n  db<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    image<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> mysql\n    environment<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> example\n    <span class=\"token comment\">#command: --default-authentication-plugin=mysql_native_password</span>\n    volumes<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> mysql<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>/var/lib/mysql\n\nvolumes<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n  mysql<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span></code></pre></div><p>Now when the MySQL is running, let's add the actual Wordpress. The container seems to require just two environment variables.</p><div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"dockerfile\"><pre class=\"language-dockerfile\"><code class=\"language-dockerfile\">  wordpress<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    image<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'wordpress:4.9.1-php7.1-apache'</span>\n    environment<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> WORDPRESS_DB_HOST=db\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> WORDPRESS_DB_PASSWORD=example\n    ports<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> <span class=\"token string\">'9999:80'</span>\n    depends_on<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> db</code></pre></div><p>We also declare that <code class=\"language-text\">db</code> service should be started first and that the container will link to it - The MySQL server is accessible with dns name \"mysql\" from the Wordpress service.</p><p>Now when you run it:</p><div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"dockerfile\"><pre class=\"language-dockerfile\"><code class=\"language-dockerfile\">$ docker<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>compose up <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>d\n$ docker<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>compose logs wordpress\n  Attaching to wordpress_wordpress_1\n  wordpress_1  <span class=\"token punctuation\">|</span> WordPress not found in /var/www/html <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> copying now<span class=\"token punctuation\">...</span>\n  wordpress_1  <span class=\"token punctuation\">|</span> Complete! WordPress has been successfully copied to /var/www/html\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">...</span></code></pre></div><p>We see that Wordpress image creates files in startup at <code class=\"language-text\">/var/www/html</code> that also needs to be persisted. The Dockerfile has this line <a href=\"https://github.com/docker-library/wordpress/blob/6a085d90853b8baffadbd3f0a41d6814a2513c11/php7.1/apache/Dockerfile#L44\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/docker-library/wordpress/blob/6a085d90853b8baffadbd3f0a41d6814a2513c11/php7.1/apache/Dockerfile#L44</a> where it declares that a volume should be created. Docker will create the volume, but it will be handled as a anonymous volume that is not managed by compose, so it's better to be explicit about the volume. With that in mind our final file should look like this:</p><div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"dockerfile\"><pre class=\"language-dockerfile\"><code class=\"language-dockerfile\">  wordpress<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    image<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'wordpress:4.9.1-php7.1-apache'</span>\n    environment<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> WORDPRESS_DB_HOST=db\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> WORDPRESS_DB_PASSWORD=example\n    ports<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> <span class=\"token string\">'9999:80'</span>\n    depends_on<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> db\n    volumes<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> wordpress<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>/var/www/html\n\nvolumes<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    mysql<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    wordpress<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span></code></pre></div><p>Now open and configure the installation at <a href=\"http://localhost:9999\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">http://localhost:9999</a></p><p>We can inspect the changes that happened in the image and ensure that no extra meaningful files got written to the container:</p><exercise name=\"Proxy\"><p>Run at wordpress.colasloth.com with</p><div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"dockerfile\"><pre class=\"language-dockerfile\"><code class=\"language-dockerfile\">  proxy<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    image<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> jwilder/nginx<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>proxy\n    volumes<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> /var/run/docker.sock<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>/tmp/docker.sock<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>ro\n    ports<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> 80<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>80</code></pre></div></exercise></div>","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-2/3-wordpress","title":"Wordpress"},"fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/matti/dev/docker-hy.github.io/data/part-2/section-3.md"},"allPages":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"dd04f2d9-efdc-5767-b1f7-aee6f17f9407","frontmatter":{"path":"/frontmatter-guide","title":"Frontmatter-guide"}}},{"node":{"id":"644a67cd-0888-5a51-8da4-e0c23358c179","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-2","title":"Part 2"}}},{"node":{"id":"c6e67bba-297f-5e4b-a933-65d9b894929e","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-1","title":"Part 1"}}},{"node":{"id":"436a4f22-5a0b-593b-a899-d682c63d8487","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-1/5-volumes-and-ports","title":"Interacting with the container via volumes and ports"}}},{"node":{"id":"643cfc84-cd7f-55c3-9d82-d7a2e22c155d","frontmatter":{"path":"/","title":"About this course"}}},{"node":{"id":"d727091a-8c5c-54d4-b5c3-b4d5d8674a39","frontmatter":{"path":"/getting-started","title":"Getting started"}}},{"node":{"id":"0b2e4a65-2b30-567c-82dd-e379d41637dd","frontmatter":{"path":"/faq","title":"Frequently asked questions"}}},{"node":{"id":"e6373e35-b266-51f8-a235-b390b59492d7","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-1/1-getting-started","title":"Definitions and basic concepts"}}},{"node":{"id":"cf1d3c45-f7be-57c3-934a-d7f924d68b44","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-1/2-running-and-stopping","title":"Running and stopping containers"}}},{"node":{"id":"6f394290-e89c-58c3-aa0d-6460c67cc55c","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-1/3-in-depth-dive-to-images","title":"In-depth dive to images"}}},{"node":{"id":"a7f190a3-6b32-544e-955b-d2143ad68bbe","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-1/7-summary","title":"Summary"}}},{"node":{"id":"2962a7c7-e916-5c7a-9f00-eb844d6541bb","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-1/4-defining-start-conditions","title":"Defining start conditions for the container"}}},{"node":{"id":"d7517b23-3158-5ea3-acb6-1a7380ec5ce6","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-2/2-docker-networking","title":"More Docker networking"}}},{"node":{"id":"2e8cfa7d-acdf-569e-a905-821d1fc0c16e","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-3/1-using-non-root-user","title":"Using a non-root user"}}},{"node":{"id":"ef09ef09-4460-59a2-a379-b3dce6ac91e5","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-2/1-migrating-to-docker-compose","title":"Migrating to docker compose"}}},{"node":{"id":"8a3f2857-0ac3-52e0-bde8-d374dc8773f1","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-3","title":"Part 3"}}},{"node":{"id":"24435d75-561c-508b-b1e7-48d4534a10b6","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-3/3-multi-host-environments","title":"Multi-host environments"}}},{"node":{"id":"6edf5e06-9b79-5149-bdc0-863b33df5f5c","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-3/2-development","title":"Development with Docker"}}},{"node":{"id":"203b5ce6-d89c-585f-8986-eecc562277b9","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-2/3-wordpress","title":"Wordpress"}}},{"node":{"id":"936a0d2b-a0e9-574d-b4b9-2cdd05866842","frontmatter":{"path":"/part-3/4-extras","title":"Extras"}}}]}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["3294351120","994120085"]}